The paper discusses structural indexing for query evaluation, which is a common topic in database systems (cs.DB). The focus is on conjunctive path queries, which are a type of graph query language, making it relevant to data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also proposes a new index based on k-path-bisimulation, which involves algorithms and computational complexity, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
